# docs/reviews/ — Review Findings

This directory holds code reviews, design reviews, and audit findings.
Review files are reference artifacts — agents can read them to understand
historical decisions, recurring patterns, and known issues.

**Important:** Files in this directory are agent work artifacts — agentify
never overwrites them. Only this README.md is maintained by agentify.

## How Agents Use This Directory

When working on code that was previously reviewed:
1. Check if a review file exists for the component or area
2. Read findings to understand known issues and prior decisions
3. Ensure new code does not re-introduce addressed findings

## File Naming Convention

`YYYY-MM-DD-type-scope.md`

Examples: `2026-05-01-code-review-auth.md`, `2026-04-15-design-review-payments.md`

Types: `code-review`, `design-review`, `security-audit`, `performance-review`

## Review File Format

```markdown
---
title: "Review title"
type: code-review | design-review | security-audit | performance-review
scope: "What was reviewed (component, PR #, date range)"
reviewer: (name or agent)
status: open | addressed | wont-fix
created: YYYY-MM-DD
---

## Summary

2-3 sentences: what was reviewed and overall assessment.

## Findings

### Critical

- **FINDING-001**: Description of the issue
  - Location: `path/to/file.ts` line N
  - Status: open | addressed | wont-fix
  - Recommendation: specific action to take

### Major

- **FINDING-002**: ...

### Minor / Suggestions

- **FINDING-003**: ...

## Decisions Made

(Design decisions or trade-offs agreed upon during the review)

## See Also

- Related component: docs/{component}.md
- Related plan: docs/plans/{plan-file}.md
```
